description: From Latin profluent, from profluere (“to flow forth”), from pro- + fluere (“to flow”).

adjectives.description: profluent (comparative more profluent, superlative most profluent)

entries.meaning: Flowing smoothly as if in a stream.
examples: My profluent waters perish not from life,Absorbed into the ever-living seaWhose life is in their full replenishment.
